Health Ministry says as of Sunday, the cumulative total of COVID-19 cases identified in South Africa is 1 231 597. A cumulative total of 7 183 893 tests have been completed with 63 046 tests conducted since the last report The recoveries now stand at 966 368, representing a recovery rate of 78,4%. South African government’s response to COVID-19:  The Health Department says regrettably, they have reported a further 339 COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 77 , Free State 19, Gauteng 28, Kwa-Zulu Natal 71, Limpopo 14, Mpumalanga 10, Northern Cape seven and Western Cape 113. This brings the total deaths to 33 163. The department conveys their condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 10 January . Use the COVID Alert SA app to protect yourself, your loved ones and your community. Start using this privacy preserving app today. Add your phone to the fight! Download the Covid Alert SA app now! https://t.co/8YKEqaiiRF pic.twitter.com/gpCyzaaIJQ — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) January 10, 2021 